Package org.rometools.feed.module.mediarss.types

This package contains datatypes for working with MediaRSS.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Reference This class is an idenfier for UrlReference and PlayerReference and is required for constructing a MediaContent object.
 

Class Summary
AbstractSchemeValue Simple data bean parent for scheme-value type entities.
Category <media:category> Allows a taxonomy to be set that gives an indication of the type of media content, and its particular contents.
Credit <media:credit> Notable entity and the contribution to the creation of the media object.
Expression expression determines if the object is a sample or the full version of the object, or even if it is a continuous stream (sample | full | nonstop).
Hash <media:hash> This is the hash of the binary media file.
MediaContent <media:content> <media:content> is a sub-element of either <item> or <media:group>.
MediaGroup <media:group> <media:group> is a sub-element of <item>.
Metadata Optional Elements The following elements are optional and may appear as sub-elements of <channel>, <item>, <media:content> and/or <media:group>.
PlayerReference <media:player> Allows the media object to be accessed through a web browser media player console.
Rating <media:rating> This allows the permissible audience to be declared.
Restriction <media:restriction> Allows restrictions to be placed on the aggregator rendering the media in the feed.
Restriction.Relationship Indicates the action of the relationship
Restriction.Type Indicated the type of the relationship
Text <media:text> Allows the inclusion of a text transcript, closed captioning, or lyrics of the media content.
Thumbnail <media:thumbnail> Allows particular images to be used as representative images for the media object.
Time Represents a RFC 2326 3.6 Normal Play Time timestamp.
UrlReference Used to indicate a URL primary reference for a MediaContent object.
 

Package org.rometools.feed.module.mediarss.types Description

This package contains datatypes for working with MediaRSS.
